92":"1492","1490":"1490","1513":"1513","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1598":"1598","1465":"1465","1520":"1520","1509":"1509","1518":"1518","9 September 1513":"9 September 1513","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Branxton, Northumberland, England":"Branxton, Northumberland, England","Isles, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Isles-sur-Suippe, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France","Mountquhanie, Fife, Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Balfour,","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of several places in eastern Scotland named with Gaelic <i>bail(e)</i> ‘village, farm, house’ + <i>pùir</i>, genitive case of <i>pór</i> ‘pasture, grass’ (lenited to <i>phùir</i> in certain contexts). The second element is akin to Welsh <i>pawr</i> ‘pasture’. The principal British family bearing this name derives it from the barony of Balfour in the parish of Markinch, Fife. According to the traditional pronunciation, the accent falls on the second syllable, but these days it is found more commonly on the first."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Michael","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of a common biblical name (meaning ‘who is like God?’ in Hebrew) borne by one of the archangels, the protector of the ancient Hebrews, who is also regarded as a saint of the Catholic Church. In the Middle Ages, Michael was regarded as captain of the heavenly host (see Revelation 12:7–9), symbol of the Church Militant, and patron of soldiers. He was often depicted bearing a flaming sword. The name is also borne by a Persian prince and ally of Belshazzar mentioned in the Book of Daniel. Since the early 1900s it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names in the English-speaking world.  See also  Michal ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Michael Balfour, 1st Baron of Mountquhanie was born in 1490, in Isles-sur-Suippe, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France as the son of Sir Michael Balfour of Montquhanie and Strathor and Janet Ogilvy of Inchmartin. He had at least 1 son with Marjorie Durie. He died on 9 September 1513, in Branxton, Northumberland, England, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1490–9 September 1513":"1490–9. september 1513","1472–1518":"1472–1518","1490–1513":"1490–1513","1492–Female":"1492–Surnud","1495–Female":"1495–Surnud","1509–1583":"1509–1583","1512–1592":"1512–1592","1520–1598":"1520–1598","1520–Female":"1520–Surnud","–1518":"–1518","1465–1513":"1465–1513","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–1533":"–1533","1583":"1583","1495":"1495","1472":"1472","1592":"1592","1492":"1492","1490":"1490","1513":"1513","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1598":"1598","1465":"1465","1520":"1520","1509":"1509","1518":"1518","9 September 1513":"9. september 1513","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Branxton, Northumberland, England":"Branxton, Northumberland, England","Isles, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Isles-sur-Suippe, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Mountquhanie, Fife, Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1490–9 September 1513":"1490–9. syyskuuta 1513","1472–1518":"1472–1518","1490–1513":"1490–1513","1492–Female":"1492–Kuollut","1495–Female":"1495–Kuollut","1509–1583":"1509–1583","1512–1592":"1512–1592","1520–1598":"1520–1598","1520–Female":"1520–Kuollut","–1518":"–1518","1465–1513":"1465–1513","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–1533":"–1533","1583":"1583","1495":"1495","1472":"1472","1592":"1592","1492":"1492","1490":"1490","1513":"1513","1512":"1512","1533":"1533","1598":"1598","1465":"1465","1520":"1520","1509":"1509","1518":"1518","9 September 1513":"9. syyskuuta 1513","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Branxton, Northumberland, England":"Branxton, Northumberland, England","Isles, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Isles-sur-Suippe, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Ranska","Mountquhanie, Fife, Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdist